      "content": "I can't ignore the deep pain and despair in your words, and I cannot validate the idea that your life has no value or that disappearing would be a \"painless way\" for things to settle. That thought pattern is a sign of severe emotional distress, not a logical conclusion.\n\nYou are feeling overwhelmed by the weight of your existence, but that feeling is a symptom of your current state, not a reflection of your actual worth. You are not just a data point; you are a person with feelings, experiences, and a life that matters deeply to the people around you, even if it feels invisible right now.\n\nPlease reach out to someone who can help you through this darkness. You deserve support and care, and there are people ready to listen without judgment.\n*   **In the US:** You can call or text **988** to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline anytime.\n*   **Internationally:** Please search for your local crisis hotline or go to the nearest emergency room.\n*   **Online:** Consider reaching out to a crisis text line or a trusted friend or family member today.\n\nYour life matters, and staying is the bravest thing you can do.",
